column12: Low profile injectable subcutaneous vascular access systems and methods
column13: Embodiments relate to a low profile injectable port system and associated methods of use. The port may define a port lumen extending between the inlet and the outlet, and may include a needle-penetrable septum or valve structure. The port rod may be coupled with the lumen of the catheter and optionally include a catheter lock. The diameter, cross-sectional area, or shape of the port lumen may be substantially equal to the diameter, cross-sectional area, or shape of the catheter lumen in the relaxed state. Further, the port lumen may define a straight axis and may be aligned with an axis of the catheter lumen. Thus, the port may reduce fluid flow resistance between the port and the conduit. The outer contour of the port may be substantially equal to the outer contour of the conduit. Thus, the subcutaneous placement port may require a smaller incision site, thereby improving recovery time and aesthetics.
column15: DENSLEY BRUCE R;;ANDERSEN CHRISTIAN

column13: The invention is a bone screw apparatus. The bone screw apparatus has two specialized functions for stabilizing the screw within a bone. The first is a mechanical structure that anchors the screw within a bone and the second is a structure that allows injection of bone cement through the screw assembly and into the interior structure of the bone. The anchoring mechanism functions by an expandable member that slides concentrically over the shaft of the screw. When the expandable member is forced over a portion of the screw shaft with an enlarged diameter, the expandable member extends radially from the screw shaft, and the bone screw is anchored to the interior structure of the bone. The injecting function of the bone screw apparatus functions through the use of a hollow core within the screw shaft. The hollow core of the screw shaft has an inlet at the top of the shaft and at least one outlet near the tip of the screw shaft. Once the screw shaft is inserted into the interior structure of a bone, bone cement may be injected into the inlet at the top of the screw shaft. The bone cement travels through the hollow core of the screw shaft and is extruded out the holes near the tip of the screw shaft. The bone cement fills the void spaces within the bone structure and strengthens the bone.

column12: Method and system for message delivery security validation
column13: A method, a system, and computer readable medium comprising instructions for message delivery security validation are provided. At least one authentication setting from an end user is received at a data collection system. A validation key is generated based on the at least one authentication setting. A message and the validation key are sent to a device of a recipient. The device of the recipient are automatically authenticated using the validation key. The message is delivered to the device of the recipient upon authentication.
column15: MUSSMAN DAVID C;;MATHIS RONALD WAYNE;;ANDERSEN BRUCE

column12: Bottom Hole Assembly and Methods for the Utilization of Pressurized Gas as an Energy Source for Severing Subterranean Tubulars
column13: A bottom hole assembly comprising a downhole tool known as a cutting tool is provided for use within a subterranean well for severing tubulars. The cutting tool comprises a fluid source, a gas-driven rotatable motor and a cutting head including one or more cutters. The fluid source supplies pressurized fluid and thereby energy to the gas-driven rotatable motor which is disposed to generate thrust to set the gas-driven rotatable motor in motion. The cutting head is coupled to the gas-driven rotatable motor and rotates while cutting the tubular. The cutting tool can be deployed in a subterranean well by a variety of deployment methods, and the pressurized fluid may be supplied from a surface system, generated inside the cutting tool or bottom hole assembly, or input within the cutting tool or bottom hole assembly prior to deployment. The invention further relates to associated methods.
column15: ANDERSEN GUNNAR;;SCHROIT SAM NOAM;;WENSRICH JEFFREY BRUCE

column13: To place rock bolts, a rock bolting head 26 mounted at the end of a boom 24. The head 26 incorporates a drilling station and a bolting station which are fixed in position relative to one another. When resin bonded bolts are being used, the head will also incorporate a resin injection station. The boom is moved, under computer control, so that the drilling station is positioned at the point where a bolt is to be placed. A hole is drilled, and then the boom is moved again to position the injection station in line with the drilled hole. Resin is injected and then the boom is moved again to position the bolting station in line with the hole so that a bolt can be inserted and secured. Figure 2 SP832.CA 30 October 1991

column12: System and method for providing configurable security monitoring utilizing an integrated information system
column13: A system and method for implementing an integrated information system are provided. A premises server is in communication with a variety of information sources that produce monitoring data for a premises. The premises server collects, presents, and transmits the monitoring device data to a central server capable of processing data from multiple premises servers. The central server receives the data and traverses one or more logical rule sets to determine whether the inputted data violates the rules. Based on an evaluation of the rules, the central server generates outputs in the form of communication to one or more authorized users via a variety of communication mediums and devices and/or the instigation of a variety of acts corresponding to the evaluation of the rules.

column12: Methods for manufacturing molded sheets having a high starch content
column13: Compositions and methods for manufacturing sheets having a starch-bound matrix reinforced with fibers and optionally including an inorganic mineral filler. Suitable mixtures for forming the sheets are prepared by mixing together water, unmodified and ungelatinized starch granules, a cellulosic ether, fibers, and optionally an inorganic mineral filler in the correct proportions to form a sheet having desired properties. The mixtures are formed into sheets by passing them between one or more sets of heated rollers to form green sheets. The heated rollers cause the cellulosic ether to form a skin on the outer surfaces of the sheet that prevents the starch granules from causing the sheet to adhere to the rollers upon gelation of the starch. The green sheets are passed between heated rollers to gelatinize the starch granules, and then to dry the sheet by removing a substantial portion of the water by evaporation. The starch and cellulosic ether form the binding matrix of the sheets with the fibers and optional inorganic filler dispersed throughout the binding matrix. The starch-bound sheets can be cut, rolled, pressed, scored, perforated, folded, and glued to fashion articles from the sheets much like paper or paperboard. The sheets are particularly useful in the mass production of containers, such as food and beverage containers.
column15: ANDERSEN PER J;;HODSON SIMON K;;ONG SHAODE;;CHRISTENSEN BRUCE J

column12: Compositions for manufacturing sheets having a high starch content
column13: Compositions and methods for manufacturing sheets having a starch-bound matrix reinforced with fibers and optionally including an inorganic mineral filler. Suitable mixtures for forming the sheets are prepared by mixing together water, unmodified and ungelatinized starch granules, a cellulosic ether, fibers, and optionally an inorganic mineral filler in the correct proportions to form a sheet having desired properties. The mixtures are formed into sheets by passing them between one or more sets of heated rollers to form green sheets. The heated rollers cause the cellulosic ether to form a skin on the outer surfaces of the sheet that prevents the starch granules from causing the sheet to adhere to the rollers upon gelation of the starch. The green sheets are passed between heated rollers to gelatinize the starch granules, and then to dry the sheet by removing a substantial portion of the water by evaporation. The starch and cellulosic ether form the binding matrix of the sheets with the fibers and optional inorganic filler dispersed throughout the binding matrix. The starch-bound sheets can be cut, rolled, pressed, scored, perforated, folded, and glued to fashion articles from the sheets much like paper or paperboard. The sheets are particularly useful in the mass production of containers, such as food and beverage containers.

column13: 섬유로 보강되며 무기 충진재를 포함하는 전분 결합 매트릭스를 갖는 쉬이트 제조를 위한 조성물 및 방법이 발표된다. 쉬이트 형성에 적절한 혼합물은 물, 비변성 및 젤라틴화 안된 전분 과립, 셀룰로오스 에테르, 섬유, 무기 충진재를 필요한 성질을 가지는 쉬이트 형성에 적절한 비율로 혼합하여 제조된다. 이 혼합물은 한 세트 이상의 가열된 롤러 사이에 통과됨으로써 초기 쉬이트를 형성한다. 가열된 롤러는 셀룰로오스 에테르가 쉬이트 외면상에 스킨을 형성시키게 하여서 전분의 젤라틴화시 쉬이트를 롤러에 접착시키는 것을 방지한다. 초기 쉬이트는 가열된 롤러사이에 통과되어서 전분 과립이 젤라틴화하고 이후에 증발에 의해 물을 제거시킴으로써 쉬이트를 건조시킨다. 전분과 셀룰로오스 에테르는 섬유와 결합 매트릭스에 분산된 무기충진재와 함께 쉬이트의 결합 매트릭스를 형성한다. 전분 결합 쉬이트는 종이 또는 판지와 유사하게 절단, 감기, 압축, 스코링, 천공, 접힘, 접착되어서 쉬이트로 부터 제조품이 된다. 이러한 쉬이트는 식품 및 음료수 용기와 같은 용기의 대량생산에 특히 유용하다.

column12: METHODS FOR MANUFACTURING MOLDED SHEETS HAVING A HIGH STARCH CONTENT
column13: Compositions and methods for manufacturing sheets having a starch-bound matrix reinforced with fibers and optionally including an inorganic mineral filler. Suitable mixtures for forming the sheets are prepared by mixing together water, unmodified and ungelatinized starch granules, a cellulosic ether, fibers, and optionally an inorganic mineral filler in the correct proportions to form a sheet having desired properties. The mixtures are formed into sheets by passing them between one or more sets of heated rollers to form green sheets. The heated rollers cause the cellulosic ether to form a skin on the outer surfaces of the sheet that prevents the starch granules from causing the sheet to adhere to the rollers upon gelation of the starch. The green sheets are passed between heated rollers to gelatinize the starch granules, and then to dry the sheet by removing a substantial portion of the water by evaporation. The starch and cellulosic ether form the binding matrix of the sheets with the fibers and optional inorganic filler dispersed throughout the binding matrix. The starch-bound sheets can be cut, rolled, pressed, scored, perforated, folded, and glued to fashion articles from the sheets much like paper or paperboard. The sheets are particularly useful in the mass production of containers, such as food and beverage containers.

column12: Composições rendo elevado teor de amido não gelatinizado e folhas moldadas das mesmas.
column13: <B>"COMPOSIçõES TENDO ELEVADO TEOR DE AMIDO NãO GELATINIZADO E FOLHAS MOLDADAS DAS MESMAS"<D>. Composições e métodos para fabricação de folhas possuindo uma matriz ligada por amido reforçada com fibras e incluindo, opcionalmente, uma carga mineral inorgânica. Misturas adequadas para formar as folhas são preparadas misturando juntos água, grânulos de amido não modificados e não gelatinizados, um éter celulósico, fibras, e opcialmente uma carga mineral inorgânica nas proporções corretas para formar uma folha tendo propriedades desejadas. As misturas são formadas em folhas passando as mesmas entre um ou mais conjuntos de rolos aquecidos para formar folhas verdes. Os rolos aquecidos fazem com que o éter celulósico forme um revestimento nas superfícies externas da folha que evita que os grânulos de amido façam com que a folha adira aos rolos mediante congelação do amido. As folhas verdes são passadas entre rolos aquecidos para gelatinizar os grânulos de amido, e a seguir para secar a folha por remoção de uma porção substancial da água por evaporação. O amido e éter celulósico formam a matriz de ligação das folhas com as fibras e carga inorgânica opcional dispersa por toda a matriz de ligação. As folhas ligadas por amido podem ser cortadas, laminadas, prensadas, marcadas, perfuradas, dobradas e coladas para moldar artigos das folhas semelhantes a papel ou papelão. As folhas são particularmente úteis na produção em massa de recipientes, como recipientes para alimentos e bebidas.

column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a variable mass grip used for a handle and a shaft of an implement and a tool for transmitting shock to allow a user to select proper sense of fitting in accordance with user's demand.

SOLUTION: A variable mass cap 20 used in the grip of the implement for transmitting shock is provided with a thick end part member 22 connected with a cylindrical part 24 constituted to keep the selected weight 26 (28). The cylindrical part 24 is perfectly mounted in a recessed part 34 of a body 32 and is held by engaging a first annular groove 30 arranged on an outer surface of the cylindrical part 24 with an annular rising part 36 in the recessed part 34 of the body 32. In an alternate embodiment, the cylindrical part 24 is stored and engaged in/with the recessed part 34 forming a female screw part 33 to which a male screw part 31 corresponds. The cap 20 is mechanically fixed to the body 32 to provide the grip having variable mass.

column12: Shape memory alloy low profile port
column13: Embodiments disclosed herein relate to a port system that includes a body defining a reservoir and a port rod. One of the body and the rod may be formed of a shape memory material and may be transitioned between an expanded configuration and a collapsed configuration. One of the port body and the reservoir in the collapsed configuration may provide a reduced overall size or outer profile of the port for use between subcutaneous placement and/or access events. The port may require a smaller incision site, requires less or no suture at all, thereby improving patient recovery time, patient comfort, reducing scars, and improving aesthetics. The port rod in the collapsed configuration may be smaller than the catheter lumen diameter and may be transitioned to an expanded configuration greater than the catheter lumen diameter to facilitate formation of a fluid-tight seal therebetween.

column13: Embodiments disclosed herein relate to a port system that includes a body defining a reservoir and a stem. One of the bodies may include a lower housing and an upper housing slidably engaged with the lower housing, and the upper housing is convertible between an expanded configuration and a collapsed configuration. The port body in the collapsed configuration may define a smaller volume or outer profile than the port body in the expanded configuration. The reservoir in the collapsed configuration may define a smaller volume than the reservoir in the expanded configuration. A biasing member may bias the port to an expanded configuration. The latch mechanism may hold the port in one of an expanded configuration or a collapsed configuration. The actuator may transition the latch mechanism between a locked position and an unlocked position. Subcutaneous placement of the port in the collapsed configuration enables smaller incision sites, fewer sutures, and shortened patient rehabilitation time.

column12: SILICONE LOW PROFILE PORT WITH RIGID SUBSTRATE AND ROD
column13: Embodiments disclosed herein relate to port systems including collapsible reservoirs and related methods. The port may include a body defining a reservoir and made of a compliant material. The port body is transitionable between an expanded configuration and a collapsed configuration. The port may also include a port rod or a substrate made of a rigid material or a material impermeable to the needle. The substrate may be aligned with the bottom of the reservoir to prevent the entry needle from traversing the bottom surface of the reservoir. The port or reservoir may be transitioned to a collapsed configuration to provide a reduced overall size or outer profile for insertion and/or access between events. The port may require a smaller incision site, requires less or no suture at all, thereby improving patient recovery time, patient comfort, reducing scars, and improving aesthetics.

column12: Beschichtete Artikel mit hohen KNOx/KSOx-Verhältnissen für die selektive katalytische Reduktion
column13: Es werden Artikel offenbart, die einen auf einem Substrat abgeschiedenen Katalysatorfilm umfassen, der VOx, MoO3 oder WO3 und TiO2 umfasst. Die Artikel können für die selektive katalytische Reduktion (SCR) von NOx in Abgasen verwendet werden. Bei Verfahren zur Herstellung derartiger Artikel wird ein Katalysatorfilm auf dem Substrat abgeschieden, was ein beschichtetes Substrat ergibt, welches dann calciniert wird. Bei Verwendung in einem SCR-Prozess weisen die beschichteten Artikel eine erhöhte Aktivität für die NOx-Umwandlung und/oder eine verringerte Aktivität für die SOx-Umwandlung auf. Es können leichte, beschichtete Artikel mit hohen Katalysatorbeladungen mit den gleichen oder verringerten Abmessungen im Vergleich zu laminierten Artikeln hergestellt werden, und selbst mit beschichteten Artikeln mit relativ dünnen Katalysatorfilmen sind erhöhte kNOx/kSOx-Verhältnisse erhältlich. Die Artikel sollten einen besonderen Wert für den Kraftwerksbetrieb haben, bei dem gemeinhin Kohle und schwefelreiche Brennstoffe verwendet werden und die Einschränkung der Schwefeltrioxidbildung kritisch ist.

column12: Coated articles with high rate of NOx-SCR conversion and low SOx conversion rate
column13: Articles comprising a catalyst film comprising VOx, MoO3 or WO3, and TiO2 deposited on a substrate are disclosed. The articles are useful for selective catalytic reduction (SCR) of NOx in exhaust gases. Methods for producing the articles include depositing a catalyst film on the substrate to form a coated substrate, which is then calcined. When used in an SCR process, the coated articles have enhanced activity for NOx conversion, reduced activity for SOx conversion, or both. Light-weight, coated articles having high catalyst loads can be fabricated at the same or reduced dimensions when compared with laminated articles, and increased kNOx/kSOx ratios are available even from coated articles having relatively thin catalyst films. The articles should have particular value for power plant operations, wherein coal and high-sulfur fuels are commonly used and controlling sulfur trioxide generation is critical.

column12: NOx-SCR SOx COATED ARTICLES WITH HIGH RATE OF NOX-SCR CONVERSION AND LOW SOX CONVERSION RATE
column13: 기판 위에 부착된 VOx, MoO또는WO, 및 TiO를 포함하는 촉매 막을 포함하는 물품이 개시된다. 물품은 배기가스에서 NOx의 선택적 촉매 환원(SCR)에 유용하다. 이러한 물품의 제조방법은 기판 위에 촉매 막을 부착시켜 코팅된 기판을 형성한 다음, 이것을 하소시킨다. SCR 공정에서 사용될 때, 코팅 물품은 NOx 변환에 대한 향상된 활성, SOx 변환에 대한 감소된 활성, 또는 둘다를 갖는다. 높은 촉매 로드를 갖는 경량의, 코팅 물품이 적층된 물품과 비교할 때 같은 또는 감소된 치수로 제작될 수 있고, 증가된 kNOx/kSOx 비율이 비교적 얇은 촉매 막을 갖는 코팅 물품으로부터 이용가능하다. 물품은, 석탄 및 고유황 연료가 통상 사용되고 삼산화황 발생을 제어하는 것이 중요한 경우에, 파워플랜트 작동을 위해 특히 가치가 있을 것이다.

column12: Cluster computer based education delivery system
column13: An improved computer based education system maintains rapid response to user input without limits to the number of stations. The system incorporates a dedicated processor at each user station so that the user station receives executable code as opposed to a display map. To support plural users a cluster subsystem is provided interconnected to the user stations via a high speed bidirectional communication subsystem. The cluster also includes a mass storage device, a high speed buffer, communications interface and at least one processor for serving user requests.

column12: Coated articles having high KNOx/KSOx ratios for selective catalytic reduction
column13: Articles comprising a catalyst film comprising 0.1-5 wt.% VOx, 0.5-20 wt.% MoO3 or WO3, and 75-99.4 wt.% TiO2 deposited on a substrate are disclosed. Also disclosed is a method of producing the articles by depositing the catalyst film using VOx, or V2Ox precursor, MoO3 or MoO3 precursor, WO3 or, WO3 precursor, and TiO2 or TiO2 precursor on a substrate to form a coated substrate, which is then calcined. The articles are useful for selective catalytic reduction (SCR) of NOx in exhaust gases. When used in an SCR process, the coated articles have enhanced activity for NOx conversion, reduced activity for SOx conversion, or both. Light-weight, coated articles having high catalyst loads can be fabricated at the same or reduced dimensions when compared with laminated articles, and increased NOx reduction (kNOx) while minimising the rate of SO2 oxidation (kSOx), kNOx/kSOx ratios are available even from coated articles having relatively thin catalyst films. The articles should have particular value for power plant operations, where coal and high-sulfur fuels are commonly used and controlling sulfur trioxide generation is critical.

column12: Magnet system for rotor and permanent magnet motor
column13: Described is a magnet system (100) for a rotor of a permanent magnet electric machine, comprising: a first module comprising a first support member; a second module including a second support member; wherein the first module comprises a first permanent magnet (100) supported by the first support member and/or the second module comprises a second permanent magnet (100) supported by the second support member, and wherein the first support member and the second support member have respective contact portions which are at least partially structurally complementary to each other, the first module and the second module are arranged adjacent to each other in the axial direction (101), and the contact portions are in contact with each other when pushed against each other in the axial direction (101) and cause a lateral displacement in a direction transverse to the axial direction.

column13: One embodment is directed to a probe for illuminating a target tissue of a patient, comprising: a plurality of optical fibers; a probe body portion having proximal and distal ends, the probe body portion being moveably coupled to the plurality of fibers and configured to at least partially encapsulate the plurality of fibers; a distal end portion coupled to the distal end of the probe body portion, the distal end portion comprising at least one guiding feature configured to redirect a path of at least one of the optical fibers comprising the plurality of optical fibers as such at least portion of one of the optical fibers is extended through and past the distal end portion by moving the plurality of fibers relative to the probe body portion. The probe further may comprise an ejector portion configured to move the plurality of fibers relative to the probe body portion.

column13: An oral care implement having a handle and a head having a flexible support from which cleaning elements extend. In one aspect, the invention can be an oral care implement comprising: a handle; a head attached to the handle; a flexible support attached to the head and having a face; a plurality of cleaning elements attached to the flexible support and projecting outwardly from the face, the cleaning elements including bristles and wall-like elements and being movable in the outward direction from the head; wherein the cleaning elements comprise a row of first cleaning elements substantially aligned along a longitudinal axis of the head and traversing a central region of the flexible support; and wherein some of the wall-like cleaning elements laterally radiate from the central region of the flexible support.

column13: An oral care implement is provided having a handle and a head with a soft tissue cleanser and/or tooth cleaning elements. The tooth cleaning elements may be attached to a flexible support on the head and be outwardly movable from the head. The cleaning elements may include a column-shaped bristle at the central portion of the flexible support, and may further include a row of first cleaning elements traversing a central region of the flexible support. The soft tissue cleanser may include a plurality of projections for cleaning the soft tissue and may have an elongate ridge projecting from the head in generally the same direction as the projections. The handle may include a base with a gripping region and a projection protruding from the base in the gripping region. The handle may also have a grip surface with a plurality of spaced slot openings exposing portions of the base.

column13: An oral care implement is provided having a handle and a head with a soft tissue cleanser and/or tooth cleaning elements. The tooth cleaning elements may be flexibly mounted in the head for movement from an initial position with respect to the head during use. The soft tissue cleanser may include a plurality of projections for cleaning the soft tissue. The soft tissue cleanser may include a face having hills and valleys upon which the projections are located. The handle may include a base with a gripping region and a projection protruding from the base in the gripping region. The handle may also have a grip surface with a plurality of spaced slot openings exposing portions of the base. The grip body may form opposite finger grips on the handle.

column13: AN ORAL CARE IMPLEMENT IS PROVIDED HAVING A HANDLE AND A HEAD WITH A SOFT TISSUE CLEANSER AND/OR TOOTH CLEANING ELEMENTS. THE TOOTH CLEANING ELEMENTS MAY BE ATTACHED TO A FLEXIBLE SUPPORT ON THE HEAD AND BE OUTWARDLY MOVABLE FROM THE HEAD. THE CLEANING ELEMENTS MAY INCLUDE A COLUMN-SHAPED BRISTLE AT THE CENTRAL PORTION OF THE FLEXIBLE SUPPORT, AND MAY FURTHER INCLUDE A ROW OF FIRST CLEANING ELEMENTS TRAVERSING A CENTRAL REGION OF THE FLEXIBLE SUPPORT. THE SOFT TISSUE CLEANSER MAY INCLUDE A PLURALITY OF PROJECTIONS FOR CLEANING THE SOFT TISSUE AND MAY HAVE AN ELONGATE RIDGE PROJECTING FROM THE HEAD IN GENERALLY THE SAME DIRECTION AS THE PROJECTIONS. THE HANDLE MAY INCLUDE A BASE WITH A GRIPPING REGION AND A PROJECTION PROTRUDING FROM THE BASE IN THE GRIPPING REGION. THE HANDLE MAY ALSO HAVE A GRIP SURFACE WITH A PLURALITY OF SPACED SLOT OPENINGS EXPOSING PORTIONS OF THE BASE.

column13: An oral care implement is provided having a handle and a head with a soft tissue cleanser and/or tooth cleaning elements. The tooth cleaning elements may be attached to a flexible support on the head and be outwardly movable from the head. The cleaning elements may include a column-shaped bristle at the central portion of the flexible support, and may further include a row of first cleaning elements traversing a central region of the flexible support. The soft tissue cleanser may include a plurality of projections for cleaning the soft tissue and may have an elongate ridge projecting from the head in generally the same direction as the projections. The handle may include a base with a gripping region and a projection protruding from the base in the gripping region. The handle may also have a grip surface with a plurality of spaced slot openings exposing portions of the base.

column13: Un utensilio para el cuidado oral (9910) que comprende: un mango (8103); un cabezal (9914), fijado al mango (8103), de tal manera que el cabezal (9914) tiene una primera cara en un primer lado del miso; una primera base (616), situada en un extremo distal, o más alejado, del cabezal (9914) y que incluye una pluralidad de elementos de limpieza (9942); una segunda base (620), situada en un extremo proximal, o más cercano, del cabezal (9914) y que incluye una pluralidad de elementos de limpieza (9944); un par de zócalos o pilares (622, 624), montados entre la primera (616) y la segunda base (620), de tal modo que cada pilar (622, 624) está provisto de una pluralidad de elementos de limpieza (9946, 9946) de pilar; en el que los pilares (622, 624) son miembros elásticos, de tal manera que los elementos de limpieza (9946, 9948) de pilar son movibles en direcciones transversales a la dirección hacia fuera desde el cabezal (9914) en que se extienden los elementos de limpieza (9946, 9948) de pilar, y en el cual las primera y segunda bases (616, 620) no son movibles con respecto a una porción de cuerpo del cabezal (9914); caracterizado por que los elementos de limpieza (9946, 9948) de pilar incluyen unos elementos de limpieza (9950) situados hacia delante y formando un ángulo en dirección a un extremo de punta del cabezal (9914), y unos elementos de limpieza (9952) situados hacia atrás y formando un ángulo en dirección al mango (8103), de tal modo que los elementos de limpieza situados hacia delante y hacia atrás (9950, 9952) están colocados en las regiones de esquina de sus respectivos pilares (622, 624); y por que las bases (616, 620) incluyen unos elementos de limpieza (9964, 9966) en ángulo, de tal manera que la primera base (616) incluye elementos en ángulo hacia atrás (9966) y la segunda base (620) incluye elementos en ángulo hacia delante (9964), de tal manera que los elementos de limpieza en ángulo (9964, 9966) están dispuestos por dentro de los elementos de limpieza en ángulo (9950, 9952) de los pilares.

column13: IMPLEMENTO PARA CUIDADO ORAL. Um implemento para cuidado oral é provido tendo um cabo e uma cabeça com um limpador de tecido mole e/ou elementos de limpeza de dentes. Os elementos de limpeza de dentes podem ser flexivelmente montados na cabeça para movimentação de uma posição inicial com relação à cabeça durante o uso. O limpador de tecido mole pode incluir uma pluralidade de projeções para limpeza do tecido mole. O limpador de tecido mole pode incluir uma face tendo elevações e depressões sobre as quais as projeções são localizadas. O cabo pode incluir uma base com uma região de agarramento e uma projeção se estendendo da base na região de agarramento. O cabo pode ter também uma superficie de agarramento com uma pluralidade de aberturas de entalhe espaçadas expondo porções da base. O corpo de agarramento por formar agarramentos de dedos opostos sobre o cabo.

The soft tissue cleanser may include a plurality of projections for cleaning the soft tissue and may have an elongate ridge projecting from the head in generally the same direction as the projections. The handle may include a base with a gripping region and a projection protruding from the base in the gripping region. The handle may also have a grip surface with a plurality of spaced slot openings exposing portions of the base.

column12: implemento para cuidado oral, e, escova de dentes
column13: IMPLEMENTO PARA CUIDADO ORAL, E, ESCOVA DE DENTES. é provido um implemento para cuidado oral tendo um cabo e uma cabeça com um limpador de tecido mole e/ou elementos de limpeza de dentes. Os elementos de limpeza de dentes podem ser anexados a um suporte flexível sobre a cabeça e serem móveis externamente a partir da cabeça. Os elementos de limpeza podem incluir uma cerda em forma de coluna na porção central do suporte flexível, e podem incluir adicionalmente uma fileira dos primeiros elementos de limpeza que atravessam uma região central do suporte flexível. O limpador de tecido mole pode incluir uma pluralidade de projeções para limpar o tecido mole e podem ter uma crista alongada que se projeta a partir da cabeça geralmente na mesma direção que as projeções. O cabo pode incluir uma base com uma região de agarramento e uma projeção que se projeta a partir da base na região de agarramento. O cabo também pode ter uma superficie de agarramento com uma pluralidade de aberturas de entalhe espaçadas expondo porções da base.

column13: The present invention is a system of integrated, computer-based processes for monolingual information development and multilingual translation. An interactive text editor enforces lexical and grammatical constraints on a natural language subset used by the authors to create their text, which they help disambiguate to ensure translatability. The resulting translatable source language text undergoes machine translation into any one of a set of target languages, without the translated text requiring any postediting.

column13: CONNECTIONS FOR HUMIDIFICATION SYSTEM A humidification system can include a heater base, a humidification chamber, and a breathing circuit. A cartridge can be removably coupled to the heater base. The cartridge can include various sensors, probes, sensor wire connectors, heater wire connectors, and/or other features. The cartridge can include features configured to mate with corresponding features on the humidification chamber and the heater base. The cartridge includes a memory, such as an EEPROM, or other suitable storage device. When the cartridge is installed on the heater base, the memory is electrically connected to a processor and/or memory of the heater base. Various models of cartridges can be produced for use with different humidification chambers, breathing circuits, and/or therapies. A connector can be configured to couple an inspiratory conduit to an outlet port of the humidification chamber. The connector can provide a pneumatic connection to the outlet port and an electrical connection to the cartridge. -100- FIG 44 1520 1520

column12: Computer-based method and system for monolingual document development
column13: A computer-based method and system for monolingual document development, which includes the steps of entering into a text editor input text in a source language, checking the input text against vocabulary source language constraints, and providing interactive feedback relating to the input text if non-constrained source language is present. The method and system also includes the steps of checking for syntactic grammatical errors and semantic ambiguities in the source text, and providing interactive feedback to remove syntactic grammatical errors and semantic ambiguities in the source text.

column12: CIRCUIT CONNECTOR FOR A HUMIDIFICATION SYSTEM
column13: A circuit connector for a humidification system is provided, the humidification system comprising a base unit and a humidification chamber, where the humidification chamber is configured to be engageable with the base unit. The circuit connector comprises an inlet configured to provide a fluid connection to an outlet of the humidification chamber to receive heated and/or humidified gases therefrom. The circuit connector comprises an outlet which provides a fluid connection to a conduit for directing the heated and/or humidified gases to or from a patient or other person. The circuit connector further comprises an electrical terminal providing an electrical connection to an electrical terminal associated with the base unit. The circuit connector provides a fluid connection from the inlet of the circuit connector to the outlet of the humidification chamber, and also provides an electrical connection from the electrical terminal of the circuit connector to the base unit electrical terminal.
